verbs.description: rechew (third-person singular simple present rechews, present participle rechewing, simple past and past participle rechewed)

examples: Nor could He (as some Beasts rechew their meat,
To cause the same the better to disgest)

entries.meaning: (figuratively) To go over or ponder again.
examples: His mind insisted on rechewing its doubts, rather than engage in constructive thought.
